# ai-skills

A collection of GitHub Copilot skills for the N-central platform engineering team.

---

## Skills

### 🔍 soap-parity-check

Analyses a single SOAP operation and produces either:
- A **Jira parity comment** — if a REST endpoint already exists (fully or partially)
- A **Jira story ticket** — if no REST equivalent exists yet

All output is in **Markdown** so it pastes cleanly into Jira's rich text editor.

Located at: `copilot/skill/soap-parity-check/SKILL.md`

---

## How to Add This Skill to Copilot

To make this skill available in a repository, add a reference to it in that repo's
`.github/copilot-instructions.md` file.

### Step 1 — Create or open `.github/copilot-instructions.md`

If the file doesn't exist yet, create it at `.github/copilot-instructions.md` in the
target repository.

### Step 2 — Add the trigger phrase

Paste the following line into the file:

```
"Run soap-parity-check for {SOAP_OPERATION_NAME} from {ServerEI|ServerUI}"
```

This tells Copilot to recognise the trigger phrase and load the skill instructions
from `Aruna-n-able/ai-skills` when it is used.

### Step 3 — Reference the skill file (optional but recommended)

If your organisation uses a skill-loading mechanism, point it at:

```
Aruna-n-able/ai-skills : copilot/skill/soap-parity-check/SKILL.md
```

### Step 4 — Use it

Open GitHub Copilot Chat in the target repo and type:

```
Run soap-parity-check for Customer.List from ServerUI
```

Copilot will read the WSDL, search for a REST implementation, produce a gap analysis,
and output a ready-to-paste Jira comment or story ticket.

---

## How to Use

### Trigger phrase

```
Run soap-parity-check for {SOAP_OPERATION_NAME} from {ServerEI|ServerUI}
```

**Examples:**

```
Run soap-parity-check for SysConfig.Get from ServerUI
```

```
Run soap-parity-check for VersionInfoGet from ServerEI
```

```
Run soap-parity-check for Customer.List from ServerUI
```

---

### Parameters

| Parameter | Description | Values |
|---|---|---|
| `SOAP_OPERATION_NAME` | The exact SOAP operation name as it appears in the WSDL | e.g. `SysConfig.Get`, `Customer.List`, `Device.Get` |
| `ServerEI` or `ServerUI` | Which WSDL file the operation belongs to | `ServerEI` → `common/ServerEI.wsdl` · `ServerUI` → `common/opeartion.wsdl` |

---

### What Copilot does

When you run the skill, Copilot will automatically:

1. **Read the WSDL** — extracts all input parameters, response fields, and complex types for the named operation
2. **Check `nable-nc/api-service`** — searches all service modules for an existing REST controller, DMS wrapper, and DTO
3. **Produce a gap analysis table** — compares every SOAP field against the REST implementation with a ��� / ⚠️ / ❌ status
4. **Output a Jira-ready result** based on what it finds:

| Finding | Output |
|---|---|
| ✅ REST fully implements SOAP | Jira **comment** with field mapping and any minor differences |
| ⚠️ REST partially implements SOAP | Jira **comment** (with gaps marked ❌) + Jira **sub-task** for the missing fields |
| ❌ No REST endpoint exists | Full Jira **story ticket** with Description, REST Endpoint, Request, Response, Error Codes, and Acceptance Criteria |

---

### Output format

All output is **Markdown** — paste directly into Jira's description or comment box using the rich text editor. No formatting mode switching needed.

#### Case A — Fully implemented → Jira Comment
Includes: Overview · Field Mapping · Request Parameter Mapping · Behavioral Differences · Missing Fields · Conclusion · Code References

#### Case B — Partially implemented → Jira Comment + Sub-task
Comment same as Case A. Sub-task includes: Background · Missing Fields to Add · Behavioural Gaps to Fix · Acceptance Criteria · Technical Notes

#### Case C — Not implemented → Jira Story Ticket

| Section | Content |
|---|---|
| **Description** | What the SOAP operation does and why REST is needed |
| **REST Endpoint** | HTTP method + URL + auth |
| **Request** | Path params · Query params · Request body (POST/PUT only) |
| **Response** | Success JSON example · typed field mapping table with SOAP → REST mapping |
| **Error Codes** | HTTP status codes and when each occurs |
| **Acceptance Criteria** | Testable checklist ready for a developer to pick up |

---

### WSDL source reference

| WSDL | File | Example operations |
|---|---|---|
| `ServerEI` | `nable-nc/api-service : common/ServerEI.wsdl` | `VersionInfoGet`, `CustomerList`, `DeviceList`, `DeviceGet` |
| `ServerUI` | `nable-nc/api-service : common/opeartion.wsdl` | `Customer.List`, `Device.Get`, `SysConfig.Get`, `AuditLog.List` |

---

### Epic

All generated tickets link to Epic **NCCF-1206785** — SOAP API to REST endpoint migration.